Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.06,0:00:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(800,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.07,0:00:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worried that this full tank of energy will lose it's destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.34,0:00:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whoever shakes for just a minute their boredom, will explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.48,0:00:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I ride, atop the white line, Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.56,0:00:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sit down, in the place you have faith Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.57,0:00:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go to the place that tempts you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.96,0:00:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each person took one thing at a time, freedom and passion in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.22,0:00:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the shine to come, continue our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:00:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unclear everyday trump-card that sustains me, is your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.55,0:01:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The best growth is coming forth, unstoppable wild drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.61,0:01:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are both yet to settle down, striking the door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.86,0:01:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retrained Elf Swordsman, attack Ipiria!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.99,0:01:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this moment, I activate my Deck Master Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.04,0:01:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So he did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.30,0:01:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice Ipiria and Youi!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.97,0:01:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And launch the Reflector Hole!!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.52,0:01:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which makes the attack of the enemy Monster invalid
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.94,0:01:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and in return steals the Attack Points from the opponent's Life Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.70,0:01:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's coming...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.59,0:01:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,''Counterattacking Rainbow Arch''
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.25,0:02:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to endure this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.04,0:02:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.97,0:02:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not too shabby. It holds 2200 Attack Points, so it could be useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But using Eingana to give a fatal strike is not entertaining in the least.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.21,0:02:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Melchid, the Four-Faced Beast in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.67,0:02:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I'll have to attack you anymore this turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.41,0:02:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but your Retrained Elf Swordsman is really an eyesore on your side of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.61,0:02:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I can't defeat him with a Monster holding 1900 Attack Points or greater,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.64,0:02:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's a really irritating Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.05,0:02:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, a less powerful Monster
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.05,0:02:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will be more than enough to strike down that Retrained Elf Swordsman of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.12,0:03:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!! Melchid, the Four-Faced Beast!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.79,0:03:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Retrained Elf Swordsman, then use your\Nremaining power to strike the enemy player!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.93,0:03:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.37,0:03:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.02,0:03:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right then, I couldn't touch the flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.32,0:04:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's going on this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.96,0:04:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Isn't this all just virtual images?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.60,0:04:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or will I be... by them...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.69,0:04:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it over?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.88,0:04:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't just sit here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere out there... the others are trying their hardest!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.42,0:04:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.22,0:04:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.02,0:04:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still have... 400 Life Points left!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.38,0:04:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This guy still has the strength to stand up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.60,0:04:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is no joke! I can't take any more damage or it'll be bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I take just one more hit, I'm in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.67,0:04:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can tell my body is throbbing in pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.51,0:04:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be much easier for you to stay down on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.08,0:05:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since you {\i1}did{\i0} stand up, I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.91,0:05:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll beat on you until you never get up {\i1}again{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thanks to that Deck Master Ability of his,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}no matter which of his Monsters on the field I attack, I'm done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.49,0:05:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Plus, my hand is at zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.69,0:05:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.66,0:05:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.53,0:05:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to give you a small present of hope as you wallow in despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.90,0:05:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Prussian General once said:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.53,0:05:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The crown of honor belongs only to the final victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.41,0:05:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The end justifies the means.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.38,0:05:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, only the one who stands victorious when all is said in done is the true winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.38,0:05:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So try your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.58,0:05:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.50,0:05:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rainbow Blessing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.91,0:05:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unfortunately, this card won't be enough to get me out of this...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.03,0:05:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, keep thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.63,0:05:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's another saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.57,0:06:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"When you have the upper hand in a pinch, you gain the courage to carry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.08,0:06:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when you face a pinch you have no control over, you lose all hope."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So do {\i1}you{\i0} have\N control over the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.68,0:06:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not good to think {\i1}too{\i0} much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.95,0:06:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuriboh... what are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.80,0:06:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I think Kuriboh's telling us to set it face-down on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.50,0:06:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think the only way to change this situation is to use your Deck Master Ability, Kuriboh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.25,0:06:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mmm-hmm!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll set one card on the field in reverse position!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.83,0:06:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.40,0:06:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's my opponent?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long do I have to wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.64,0:06:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out here already so we can start the Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.34,0:07:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.16,0:07:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to get away from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.29,0:07:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to... rescue me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.07,0:08:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on with this sense of reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this Virtual Reality really this revolutionary of a system?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.68,0:08:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Virtual Reality that imitates feeling...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.74,0:08:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still way too naive, Seto...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.96,0:08:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The system that you built had a safe-guarding device that didn't harm the human brain or body.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.67,0:08:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this Virtual Reality...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.20,0:08:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like there's no safe-guard installed at {\i1}all{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.17,0:08:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a dangerous atmosphere everywhere around this space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.22,0:08:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this Noah thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.23,0:08:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you've got something to say, say it to my face!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.86,0:08:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.83,0:08:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.18,0:08:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the road we're walking now, we have no need to look into the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.32,0:09:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, the things I care the most about haven't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.94,0:09:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Mokuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.64,0:09:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.02,0:09:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.29,0:09:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.83,0:09:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Instant Quick-Play Magic, Offerings to the Dead, from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.30,0:09:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I destroy the only thing you've got to attack me with, Chimera!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.01,0:09:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the effect of Offerings to the Dead, I can destroy one of your Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.33,0:09:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... the Special Ability that activates only when Chimera is destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.59,0:09:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...lets me Special Summon Berfomet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.96,0:10:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh. Your situation hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.10,0:10:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, you could even say it's getting {\i1}worse{\i0} for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.60,0:10:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.79,0:10:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll then sacrifice Melchid the Four-Faced Beast and Wall of Illusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.31,0:10:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to Summon Rainbow Snake Eingana!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.85,0:10:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Rainbow Snake Eingana to attack Berfomet!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then... You've lost your wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.57,0:10:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like a castle that has had its walls breached.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.28,0:10:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I only have 400 Life Points left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.57,0:10:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And after being attacked by his Ruklomba, I'll be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.89,0:10:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to {\i1}really{\i0} put an end to things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.79,0:11:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They see me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.83,0:11:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, let me launch the final attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.54,0:11:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will finally get a body back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.14,0:11:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.10,0:11:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Ruklomba the Spirit King to directly attack the player!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.91,0:11:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Ruklomba!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.78,0:11:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the end?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.98,0:11:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.59,0:12:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the {\i1}world{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.86,0:12:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you... reduce his Life Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.18,0:12:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Kuriboh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.18,0:12:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You changed to Type A Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.76,0:12:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't your Life Points gone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.16,0:12:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because my Deck Master's, Kuriboh's, Ability lets him multiply and create the Protection Wall for the player!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.19,0:12:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Partner... why did you switch with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.03,0:12:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if you take any more damage from him, your mental state will suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.20,0:12:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I haven't taken any damage yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.37,0:12:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Partner... thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.34,0:12:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be thanking Kuriboh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.18,0:13:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of Kuriboh's Protection Wall, my Life Points were protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.08,0:13:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.26,0:13:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I guess that's Kuriboh's Deck Master Ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.15,0:13:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under this system... the Duelist who can unite with the heart of their Deck Master has the upper hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.03,0:13:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, it's only natural for a Duelist to bond with the heart of their Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.21,0:13:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.93,0:13:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Perhaps I've forgotten\N the most important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Partner!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.57,0:13:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although our Life isn't gone, the mental trauma was too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.41,0:13:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the rest to me and Kuriboh!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.33,0:13:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saved by your\N Deck Master's Ability, were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.35,0:13:47.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't forget about the risk of Summoning your Deck Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.44,0:13:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When your Deck Master is destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.94,0:13:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,regardless of whether you have lost all of your Life, you lose the Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.86,0:13:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuriboh can't be compared with my Monsters. It cannot withstand my next attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.44,0:14:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, when I deliver the final attack, you {\i1}really will{\i0} be finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.28,0:14:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't give this Duel up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.07,0:14:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.16,0:15:00.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.03,0:15:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look! This is the proof of our friendship!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.81,0:15:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Right! Even if we we're apart, we'll be marked and tied to each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.92,0:15:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everyone's trying there best out there somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.72,0:15:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You have to be courageous, Anzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.75,0:16:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.62,0:16:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait... I told you to go away! The bridge will collapse!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.51,0:16:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on already~!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.87,0:17:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell am I gonna die {\i1}here{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.13,0:17:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.80,0:17:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I won't lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.42,0:17:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just like he said... if I don't win the match this turn, I have no hope of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.45,0:17:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.73,0:17:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Kuriboh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:25.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Duelist and their Deck Master share one heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.14,0:17:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll decide this with one draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.74,0:17:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.27,0:17:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have something to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.27,0:17:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many ancient proverbs you've memorized and recited, they aren't your {\i1}own words{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.68,0:17:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should mold them into your {\i1}own{\i0} words.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.81,0:17:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The crown of honor belongs only to the final victor."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.78,0:17:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the words you said {\i1}yourself{\i0} earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.98,0:17:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, I'm gonna make them into my {\i1}own{\i0} words and give them {\i1}back{\i0} to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.83,0:17:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be euphemistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.36,0:17:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what are you playing at?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.60,0:18:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.02,0:18:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gale Dark Knight Gaia?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.01,0:18:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.64,0:18:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My combo is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.93,0:18:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how powerful the Monsters you play may be, your attacks still won't work on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.85,0:18:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as there's a gap between your Life Points and mine, you cannot turn the tables.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.49,0:18:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that {\i1}so{\i0} now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.24,0:18:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse Card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.41,0:18:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card! Rainbow Blessing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.26,0:18:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will then proceed to equip Rainbow Blessing with my Deck Master, Kuriboh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.49,0:18:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.26,0:18:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Kuriboh!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.14,0:18:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rainbow Arch!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.26,0:18:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rainbow Arch?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.75,0:19:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you trying to pull?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.25,0:19:04.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll then Summon Gale Dark Knight Gaia in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.80,0:19:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth!\N Gale Dark Knight Gaia!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.93,0:19:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Rainbow Arch created by Rainbow's Blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.79,0:19:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,allows him to pass over enemy Monsters and Direct Attack the player!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.75,0:19:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! There's no way Kuriboh has such an Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.85,0:19:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Gale Dark Knight Gaia!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.92,0:19:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct Attack the Deepsea Warrior!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.75,0:19:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.43,0:19:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't use my Deck Master Ability against Direct Attacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.95,0:19:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.28,0:19:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Deck Master Ability is only effective when I attack your {\i1}Monsters{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.02,0:19:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.24,0:19:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I almost got myself a body...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.08,0:20:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and came so close to returning to the real world!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.74,0:20:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I managed to win...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.96,0:20:22.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This damage... is way too dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.64,0:20:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do all the others have to take part in Duels like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.04,0:20:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Kuriboh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.49,0:20:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Yugi really {\i1}was{\i0} as strong as the rumors state, eh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.45,0:20:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or perhaps the prestigious Big Five members who wandered the Cyber World for so long...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.46,0:20:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...were only capable of this much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.51,0:20:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I do hope they will entertain me more in the upcoming Duels.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.33,0:21:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's an exit! We made it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.47,0:21:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.51,0:21:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go, I'm worried about the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.57,0:21:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.69,0:21:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't hurry and find and help them soon, their Duels might be too much for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.48,0:21:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(127,113)}"Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.11,0:21:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when I finally escaped the Cyclops that were chasing me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.53,0:21:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a bunch of penguins\N appear before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.33,0:21:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Follow us"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.96,0:21:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where exactly are you taking me...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.63,0:21:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hu- what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.14,0:21:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's {\i1}so many{\i0} penguins!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.02,0:21:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could this really be\N one of the Big Five's traps?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.48,0:22:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! If that's the case, whether it's a Duel or whatever, I'll take you on!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.08,0:22:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.75,0:22:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Iceberg Duel: Anzu Targeted"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.30,0:22:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.59,0:22:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, wherever it rises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.50,0:22:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A dream is a dream, and it won't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.77,0:22:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The straight rail and the steep route
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.45,0:22:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go, or not go all of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.84,0:22:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm getting tired of counting my advances in a cage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.40,0:22:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Respect! Boys, show me your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.99,0:22:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's awkward, but draw the map
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.76,0:23:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now let's walk forever with our head up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.91,0:23:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, if it starts to get to familiar like you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.72,0:23:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}answer freely to the everyday discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.50,0:23:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe you, because I am losing my way with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.48,0:23:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hiding in my heart... this secret paradise
